 To install zip and unzip on Ubuntu, you can use the standard package manager (apt). Use the following command to install both at once: [1, 2]
bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install zip unzip
يُرجى استخدام الرمز البرمجي بحذر.
Installation Steps
    1. Update Package List: It is good practice to update your local package index before installing new software.
       bash
       sudo apt update
       يُرجى استخدام الرمز البرمجي بحذر.
    2. Install the Utilities: Run the installation command for both tools.
       bash
       sudo apt install zip unzip
       يُرجى استخدام الرمز البرمجي بحذر.
    3. Verify Installation: You can confirm they were installed correctly by checking their versions.
        ◦ For zip: zip -v
        ◦ For unzip: unzip -v [1, 2, 3, 4]
Basic Usage
Once installed, you can use these common commands:
    • Zip a file/folder:
        ◦ Single file: zip archive_name.zip file.txt
        ◦ A directory (recursively): zip -r archive_name.zip folder_name/
    • Unzip an archive:
        ◦ To current directory: unzip archive_name.zip
        ◦ To a specific directory: unzip archive_name.zip -d /path/to/destination/
    • List contents without extracting: unzip -l archive_name.zip [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]

